1. Core AWS Services (Deep Level)

  Compute
    . EC2 (networking, storage, AMIs, autoscaling, spot)
    . ECS, EKS (full production deployments)
    . Lambda (event-driven design, cold start tuning)

  Networking
    . VPC design (CIDR planning, multi-VPC)
    . IGW, NAT, Transit Gateway
    . PrivateLink, VPC Peering
    . Hybrid connectivity (VPN, Direct Connect)
    . Route 53 (routing policies, failover, latency, geoprox)

  Storage
    . S3 (versioning, lifecycle, replication, encryption)
    . EBS, EFS, FSx
    . Data durability and performance tuning

2. Security & Identity
  . IAM (least privilege design, SCPs, permission boundaries)
  . KMS (key policies, envelope encryption)
  . Secrets Manager vs Parameter Store
  . CloudTrail, Config, GuardDuty, Security Hub
  . WAF + Shield advanced configurations
  . Multi-account security architecture (Control Tower)

3. Automation & IaC
  . Terraform (preferred in industry)
  . CloudFormation (advanced templates, modules, stacks)
  . CI/CD (CodePipeline, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI)
  . Automated deployments (blue/green, canary)

4. Containers & Orchestration
  . EKS (cluster networking, IRSA, node groups, addons)
  . ECS/Fargate deployments
  . Service mesh basics (App Mesh, Envoy)
  . Container security and observability

5. Monitoring & Observability
 . CloudWatch (logs, metrics, alarms)
 . Distributed tracing (X-Ray, OpenTelemetry)
 . Centralized logging (Kinesis → S3 → Athena)
 . Performance troubleshooting

6. Databases
  . RDS (backups, failover, parameter groups)
  . DynamoDB (indexes, TTL, streams, capacity planning)
  . Aurora (serverless v2, replicas, autoscaling)
  . ElastiCache (Redis clusters/sharding)

7. Scaling, Availability, Resilience
  . Multi-AZ and Multi-Region architecture
  . Disaster recovery patterns:
    . Backup & Restore
    . Pilot Light
    . Warm Standby
    . Multi-region active-active
  . Load balancing (ALB, NLB, GWLB)

8. Cost Optimization
  . Compute savings plans
  . Spot strategies
  . S3 storage classes & lifecycle
  . Cost Explorer analysis
  . Rightsizing + auto-scheduling


9. Data Engineering Basics (Very Important Now)
  . Glue, Athena, EMR basics
  . S3 data lake patterns
  . Lambda + Kinesis pipelines

10. Soft Skills
  . Architecture decision-making
  . Production incident handling
  . Clear documentation and diagrams
  . Reviewing infra/app code
  
